<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="223" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="1.[136,778,1603,2092]" pageId="1" pageNumber="223">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,242,1603,1627]" pageId="1" pageNumber="223">Material.</emphasis>
Specimen number AD-33; well-preserved immature psocodean (
<figureCitation box="[263,379,1642,1667]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[136,235,1448,1472]" captionTargetBox="[275,1313,174,1424]" captionTargetId="figure-231@1.[275,1313,174,1424]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Immature psocodean, specimen number AD-33. A, Habitus in dorsal view. B, Habitus in ventral view. C, Details of labial palpomeres and lacinia. D, Details of claws (arrow indicating preapical tooth). Scale bars = 0.3 mm for A, 0.5 mm for B, 0.05 mm for C, 0.03 mm for D." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6820806" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6820806/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="223">Fig. 1A, B</figureCitation>
), female; no syninclusions.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[136,778,1603,2092]" pageId="1" pageNumber="223">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,429,1681,1705]" pageId="1" pageNumber="223">Locality and horizon.</emphasis>
Ain Dara, CazaAley, Mouhafazit Jabal Loubnan (
<collectingRegion box="[320,652,1720,1744]" country="Lebanon" name="Mont-Liban" pageId="1" pageNumber="223">Mount Lebanon Governorate</collectingRegion>
), 
<collectingCountry box="[677,774,1720,1744]" name="Lebanon" pageId="1" pageNumber="223">Lebanon</collectingCountry>
; Lower Cretaceous, lower Barremian (
<bibRefCitation author="Maksoud, S. &amp; Azar, D. &amp; Granier, B. &amp; Geze, R." box="[541,774,1759,1783]" pageId="1" pageNumber="223" pagination="331 - 338" refId="ref2335" refString="Maksoud, S., Azar, D., Granier, B. &amp; Geze, R. (2017) New data on the age of the Lower Cretaceous amber outcrops of Lebanon. Palaeoworld, 26 (2), 331 - 338. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. palwor. 2016.03.003" type="journal article" year="2017">
Maksoud 
<emphasis box="[649,703,1759,1783]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="223">et al.</emphasis>
, 2017
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Maksoud, S. &amp; Azar, D." box="[136,390,1797,1821]" pageId="1" pageNumber="223" pagination="125 - 155" refId="ref2294" refString="Maksoud, S. &amp; Azar, D. (2020) Lebanese amber: latest updates. Palaeoentomology, 3 (2), 125 - 155. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / palaeoentomology. 3.2.2" type="journal article" year="2020">Maksoud &amp; Azar, 2020</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="224" pageId="1" pageNumber="223" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[136,778,1603,2092]" lastBlockId="2.[136,778,1451,1547]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="224" pageId="1" pageNumber="223">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,328,1836,1860]" pageId="1" pageNumber="223">Description.</emphasis>
Head: Measurements in dorsal view, around 
<quantity box="[218,314,1875,1899]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5999999999999996" pageId="1" pageNumber="223" unit="mm" value="0.36">0.36 mm</quantity>
wide (compound eyes included), 
<quantity box="[682,777,1875,1899]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1" pageId="1" pageNumber="223" unit="mm" value="0.21">0.21 mm</quantity>
wide (vertex); epicranial suture faintly visible; no ocelli, large compound eyes globulous, semi-circular in dorsal view, 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" pageId="1" pageNumber="223" unit="mm" value="0.14">0.14 mm</quantity>
long, protruding with a width of 
<quantity box="[541,640,1991,2015]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7" pageId="1" pageNumber="223" unit="mm" value="0.07">0.07 mm</quantity>
; left antenna almost complete, with 15 antennomeres preserved, shorter than body length; mouthparts unclear due to specimen distortion, fractions in amber and mirror effect, maxillary palp four-segmented, labial palp two-segmented, lacinia present (
<figureCitation box="[911,1005,1680,1704]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[136,235,1448,1472]" captionTargetBox="[275,1313,174,1424]" captionTargetId="figure-231@1.[275,1313,174,1424]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Immature psocodean, specimen number AD-33. A, Habitus in dorsal view. B, Habitus in ventral view. C, Details of labial palpomeres and lacinia. D, Details of claws (arrow indicating preapical tooth). Scale bars = 0.3 mm for A, 0.5 mm for B, 0.05 mm for C, 0.03 mm for D." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6820806" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6820806/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="223">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
). Thorax: mesonotum and metanotum almost of equal length, both 
<quantity box="[1108,1200,1719,1743]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="223" unit="mm" value="0.3">0.30 mm</quantity>
long; wing buds visible on both thoracic segments; tibiae slender, setose with two apical spurs; all tarsi two-segmented, ratio of basal to apical segment: in fore and mid legs 1:1, in hind legs 1.8:1, basal tarsomere with two apical spurs, apical tarsomere bearing claws with one preapical tooth (
<figureCitation box="[1147,1230,1913,1937]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[136,235,1448,1472]" captionTargetBox="[275,1313,174,1424]" captionTargetId="figure-231@1.[275,1313,174,1424]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Immature psocodean, specimen number AD-33. A, Habitus in dorsal view. B, Habitus in ventral view. C, Details of labial palpomeres and lacinia. D, Details of claws (arrow indicating preapical tooth). Scale bars = 0.3 mm for A, 0.5 mm for B, 0.05 mm for C, 0.03 mm for D." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6820806" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6820806/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="223">Fig. 1D</figureCitation>
), without empodium or pulvillus. Abdomen: ten segments visible, with multiple glandular structures clustered mainly along the edge of each abdominal segment (
<figureCitation box="[1032,1098,2029,2053]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[136,235,772,796]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,174,748]" captionTargetId="figure-285@2.[189,1398,174,748]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Abdominal glandular structures. A, General view. B, Detailed view. Scale bars = 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6820808" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6820808/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="223">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
); epiproct apically rounded, with seven long spurs; two lobe-like structures bearing one short spine each (paraprocts?); genitalia not fully developed, but of female 
<typeStatus box="[244,293,1488,1512]" pageId="2" pageNumber="224">type</typeStatus>
, with two distinct structures bearing long and thick spines apically (
<figureCitation box="[368,433,1523,1547]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="2.[136,235,1368,1392]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,828,1345]" captionTargetId="figure-306@2.[189,1398,828,1345]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 3. Details of terminalia. A, Photograph. B, Illustration. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6820810" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6820810/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="224">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
